sentences: Kjetil Saunes (born 22 October 1962 in Ulsteinvik, Norway) is a Norwegian musician (bass), composer and songwriter raised in, and still residing in, Oslo.
Saunes started his musical career as 19 years old, in a band including Kjetil Bjerkestrand, Anders Viken and Eivind Aarset.
In the 80s he played with the KGB, a Christian rock band from Hamar.
Reisetid (September), with Ketil Bjørnstad including Eldbjørg Raknes, Petronella Barker & Henrik Mestad
2003: Hurricane's Eye (St. Cecilia Music), with Unni Wilhelmsen
